movies.label: Sound It Out
movies.title: Sound It Out
movies.plot: Over the last five years an independent record shop has closed in the UK every three days.  SOUND IT OUT is a documentary portrait of the very last surviving vinyl record shop in Teesside, North East England.  A cultural haven in one of the most deprived areas in the UK, SOUND IT OUT documents a place that is thriving against the odds and the local community that keeps it alive. Directed by Jeanie Finlay who grew up three miles from the shop.  A distinctive, funny and intimate film about men, the North and the irreplaceable role music plays in our lives.  High Fidelity with a Northern Accent.
